    {
      "name": "Ukraine",
      "isActive": true,
      "meta": {
        "description": "This interactive map shows the results of the **Delineate Anything** algorithm applied to the detection of field boundaries across *Ukraine*.  Data is displayed on high resolution satellite imagery from the Stadia Maps service.\n\nTo view the field boundaries zoom in to a local area anywhere within the *Ukraine*.  The boundaries are displayed on the map when the scalebar in the bottom left displays **5 km** or less.\n\n### Further information\nDetails of methodology and code published in: \n* [Article](https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.02534)\n* [GitHub repository](https://github.com/Lavreniuk/Delineate-Anything)\n\n### Authors\n[Mykola Lavreniuk](https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=-oFR-RYAAAAJ) (1,2), [Nataliia Kussul](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=e3TWBuwAAAAJ&hl=en) (3), [Andrii Shelestov](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=tqoQKZAAAAAJ&hl=en) (2,4), [Bohdan Yailymov](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=XaN-oukAAAAJ&hl=en) (2), [Yevhenii Salii](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=4jgAsBIAAAAJ&hl=en) (2,4), [Volodymyr Kuzin](https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Volodymyr-Kuzin) (2,4), [Zoltan Szantoi](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=P_pyhi8AAAAJ&hl=en) (1)\n\n[1] European Space Agency, [2] SRI NASU-SSAU, [3] University of Maryland, [4] Igor Sikorsky Kyiv Polytechnic Institute",
        "attribution": {
          "text": ""
        },
        "categories": []
      },
